Your problem is that unsetting values in the loop is changing the `count` of the array of the array, and so you are never actually looking at `$arr[4]` to decide whether to unset it. Pre-compute the `count` and your loop will work:

    public static function filterNumbersFromArray(&amp;$arr)
    {
        $i = 0;
        $c = count($arr);
        while ($i &lt; $c) {
            if(is_integer($arr[$i]) === false){
                unset($arr[$i]);
            }
            $i++;
        }
    }

